article.headline: Campbell 85, Stetson 55
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Junard Hartley scored 16 points and Campbell routed Stetson 85-55 on Saturday to snap a three-game losing streak. Campbell led 41-26 at halftime and the lead was at least 20 points for the final 16 minutes of the game. A layup by Marvelle Harris with 2:05 remaining gave the Camels their biggest lead of the game at 83-52. The Camels scored 26 points off 15 Stetson turnovers and outscored the Hatters in the paint 38-20. Campbell also had a 37-22 rebounding edge. Eric Griffin had 13 points and 10 rebounds, and Preston Dodson added 10 points for Campbell (10-9, 4-6). Stetson made only eight field goals in the second half and shot 41.3 percent (19 of 46) for the game while Campbell made 52.8 percent (28 of 53) of its field goal attempts. Steve Forbes and Corey Walden each had nine points to lead the Hatters (6-14, 4-5), who lost their third consecutive game.
